info: Rating, 1 star,  · April 2024,  · Stayed a few nights
rating_comment: i am sorry but its not a residential building. the entire buiding is occupied with business offices. there was no guards or security at the gate. the landlord said that the guard was on vacation! during the check in the gate was locked and throughout the stay the gate was open without any locks or a guard. the listing is on the top of the buiding, guess what, the elevator was not turned on. the place was warm like an oven because of all the sunlight (work like a green house). I just felt like an uninvited guest. laslty, Ahnaf! there was no Ahnaf, a guy introduced him as the landlord holding all the keys said Ahnaf (son) was not home, he gave us his number and told us to communicate with him. I am sorry, but I didn't feel safe there.

info: Rating, 5 stars,  · November 2023,  · Stayed about a week
rating_comment:
The place is very good for couples and single people, for both vacation and work trips. It's located in a prominent, secure residential area in Dhaka.
The penthouse itself and its premises are very well maintained. Salam Bhai, the building caretaker, deserves special praise. He provided exceptional service and made sure I had everything to enjoy my stay.
Mosquitoes can be an issue. Please make sure to be prepared. Bring sprays, lotion etc to avoid mosquito bites.
I would definitely book again. Highly recommend.

info: Rating, 5 stars,  · June 2023,  · Stayed over a week
rating_comment: A beautiful place to stay. Very secured and well maintained. Caretaker Salam is a wonderful person. He was extremely helpful throughout my stay. I had some repeated issues with the AC during my 23 day stay but was taken care of in a timely manner. One area that need improvement is the washroom! Overall it’s a great place to stay.
